0. Requirements:

	0.1 - Java
	    >= Latest 1.6, 32/ 64-bit

	0.2 - Simple Build Tool (sbt)
	    >= 0.7.4

	0.3 - Scala (will be downloaded by sbt)
	    >= 2.8.1
	    
    0.4 - ZSH Shell
        >= 4.3.10
        
    0.5 - Sudo
        >= 1.7.4p6
    
	0.6 - Sigar library
	    >= 1.6.3.82
	    
	0.7 - Smack library (for XMPP Notifications)
	    >= 3.0.4

    0.8 - pIRCbot library (for IRC Notifications)
        >= 1.4.2
        
	0.9 - List of currently supported platforms:
	    Mac OSX (100% features, development),
	    Free BSD (100% features, production),



1. Instalation
    1.1 - install native libraries from "libs.native.64" folder (currently only 64bit systems are fully supported)
        In FreeBSD 8.1:
            A. Become superuser (root):
                * sudo -i
            B. Install ports:
                * portsnap fetch
                * portsnap extract
            C. Install OpenJDK6 (OpenJDK7 will be supported parallely)
                * unset JAVA_HOME
                * cd /usr/ports/java/openjdk6 && make install
                * follow requirements and instructions
	1.2 - sbt "project SvdMaintainer" run



2. Testing
    2.1 - Use sbt test

That's all folks



